f the axis drive cards greatlly expanding the applicability of the mxc allied motion can work with you to define and develop these auxiliary cards to suit your specific application demandsthe master control card handles all higher level motion control operations and feeds command information to the axis drive cards it also handles all communication with a host controller or pc if presentthe mxcs master module is equipped with an ethernet port enabling high speed communication with a system controller or host pcthe mxc will also able run in standalone mode with no need for a host the mxcs multitasking preemptive runtime environment is capable of running several program blocks called pobs simultaneously pobs can be downloaded and executed on the fly or recalled and run from local non volatile storage at powerup the run time environment also features an extensive programmable event driven mechanism for starting and stopping program blocks based upon such factors as a change of io state or a reaction to a fieldbus messageallied motion provides complimentary in control software with the mxc in control is a windowsbased development and control software application for use with the mxc and other allied motion drive and controller products in control enables you to easily setup and configure the mxc it includes a four channel software oscilloscope tool that provides data logging of system registers in real time in control also provides tools for system setup analysis diagnostics io and eventresponse configurationcompact modular multiaxis motion controller capable of controlling up to six servo axeseach drive module can deliver up to  w of continuous powerin control software makes it easy to setup configure and program the mxc motion controllerkey features  benefitscontrol modes position torque and velocity modes available during commissioningmotor types accommodated brushless brush stepperauto run execute stored programs from flashin control software setup and programming software that includes digital oscilloscope and frequency analysis toolsaxis drive current  a or  a peakaxis drive voltage  to  vdcdigital io master and axis cards isolated inputsup to  high speed differential pairs configurable as inputs or outputs isolated outputs nonisolated output opencollectoranalog io differential inputs ±v  bits master  bits axis analog output    v  bits axispower inputs main dc power input and separate auxiliary keep alive inputencoders accommodated singleended differential incremental analog interpolation to  times endat  up to  bissc up to size very compact ¨ x ¨ x ¨  mm x  mm x  mmsystem communication ethernet  mbs to host or pc plus rsspi interface enables connection of peripheral devices such as camerasoperating temperature wide temperature operating range of  to  °ccompliance rohsspecificationsarchitecturedc powered modular multiaxis motion controller with master module two axis drive modules optional expanded io moduleaxessupply voltage   vdclogic power to  vdc to maintain logic power during main power shut offoutput voltage max vdcoutput current cont a total rack limit of  a continuous must be observedoutput current peak aoutput power cont w per  a drive total output power all axes must be   wefficiency  at  ºcmotor compatibilitybrushless servomotors linear or rotary sinusoidal or trapezoidal commutation step motorscurrent torque looppi  μs loop delayvelocity looppidpdf  μs loop delayposition loopproportional with feed forward  µsec updateposition modespointtopoint target position with velocityaccelerationjerk limitsmotor feedback inputsencoder  mhz digital incremental  mhz analog sincos sincos interpolation up to times endat  support of endat  command set up to  bissc up to  custommotion typesposition velocity torque current control  khz torque loop update rate  khz veloicity and position loop update rates pid  feedforward userconfigurable digital filters eg notch low pass setpoint streamingacceleration controlthird order position ve